Go to your project folder.
Initialize Git: git init
Create a new branch: git checkout -b branch_name
Add the files/folders you want: git add path/to/files
Commit your changes: git commit -m "commit message"
Add remote repo if not added: git remote add origin repo_url
Push the branch: git push -u origin branch_name
Your main branch stays untouched.
You can now create a pull request on GitHub if needed.
